$ GNU Autoconf
@ Autoconf

Autoconf is an extensible package of M4 macros that produce shell scripts to automatically configure software source code packages.

Autoconf tests for available features rather than for installed versions.

Based on the input of a → development/GNU/toolchain/Build-System/configure_ac file, Autoconf generates a shell script: → development/GNU/toolchain/Build-System/configure.

Autoconf requires GNU M4 version 1.4.6 or later in order to generate the scripts.

sa:
  → development/GNU/toolchain/Build-System[GNU Build System]

  → Linux/fhs/usr/share/autoconf

links:
  → http://savannah.gnu.org/projects/autoconf/, → https://www.gnu.org/software/autoconf/autoconf.html,
